<item>
            <title>[MATH-989] Allow code to avoid OutOfRangeException</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MATH-989</link>
                <project id="12310485" key="MATH">Commons Math</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Exceptions are generally costlier than a test. In the BicubicSplineInterpolatingFunction, there is no way to determine if a given x is in domain of the interpolator. So, I suggest a function to allow this check.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12650935">MATH-989</key>
            <summary>Allow code to avoid OutOfRangeException</summary>
